The paper proposes a new approach to generalization for deep neural networks when used for supervised learning. It involves using a collaborative generative network to produce new synthetic data points in the form of perturbations of original data points. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
